Derived by applying decode logic on ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime columns in DimSupportServiceRequest table coming from SA&DP Commercial Source. Logic: calculate new column Range-when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime < 0 then '<=0' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 0 and <=1 then '>0-1' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 1 and <=2 then '>1-2' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 2 and <=3 then '>2-3' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 3 and <=4 then '>3-4' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 4 and <=5 then '>4-5',when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 5 and <=6 then '>5-6' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 6 and <=7 then '>6-7' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 7 and <=14 then '>7-14' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 14 and <=21 then '>14-21' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 21 and <=30 then '>21-30' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 30 and <=60 then '>30-60' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 60 and <=90 then '>60-90' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 90 and <=120 then '>90-120' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime >120 then '>120' . Now join DimRange based on this new Range column and extract RangeKey

This is a reference key to DimRange table to get more details about Ticket ageRange. Derived by applying decode logic on ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime columns in DimSupportServiceRequest table coming from SA&DP Commercial Source. Logic: calculate new column Range-when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime < 0 then '<=0' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 0 and <=1 then '>0-1' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 1 and <=2 then '>1-2' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 2 and <=3 then '>2-3' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 3 and <=4 then '>3-4' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 4 and <=5 then '>4-5',when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 5 and <=6 then '>5-6' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 6 and <=7 then '>6-7' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 7 and <=14 then '>7-14' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 14 and <=21 then '>14-21' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 21 and <=30 then '>21-30' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 30 and <=60 then '>30-60' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 60 and <=90 then '>60-90' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime is > 90 and <=120 then '>90-120' ,when datedifference of ClosedDateTime,CreatedDateTime >120 then '>120' . Now join DimRange based on this new Range column and extract RangeKey

logic:Step 1:When msdyn_agentacceptedon is 0 ,hardcoded Status attribute as Abandoned, and when Status is Abandoned hardcoded IsAbandoned as 1
Step 2: Creating WaitSeconds column by applying logic like Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and Session.msdyn_sessioncreatedon and
Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and msdyn_ocliveworkitem.msdyn_createdon ,and unioning all the data
Step 3: case when IsAbandoned is 1 (Status is Abandoned) and waitseconds is less than 9 then hardcoded as 1 for records System Abandoned otherwise hardcoded as 0 for records System not Abandoned"

"Derived by applying decode logic on msdyn_agentacceptedon and WaitTimeInMilliSeconds columns from msdyn_ocliveworkitem and session table, coming from cornerstone source  logic:Step 1: Creating IsAgentAccept_check attribute based on a Case statement When Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon isNull() hardcoded as 0 otherwise 1

Step 3: Creating WaitSeconds column by applying logic like Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and Session.msdyn_sessioncreatedon logic:(Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon-Session.msdyn_sessioncreatedon ) and
Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and msdyn_ocliveworkitem.msdyn_createdon logic:(Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon-OCLiveWorkitem.msdyn_createdon) ,and unioning all the data
Step 4: Total number of millseconds to close ticket is calculated based on WaitSeconds column and renaming it to WaitTimeInMilliSeconds logic : WaitSeconds*1000
Step 5:Case when IsAbandoned=0 (Status is Abandoned) and WaitTimeInMilliSeconds = 0 then hardcoded as 1 for records Abandoned in 0 seconds otherwise hardcoded as 0 for records not Abandoned in 0 seconds"""""""

This attribute is calculated using columns conversationId,participantId columns coming from MessageRecords section in LivePerson Messaging API source. Logic: It is theSet to 1 if assigned agent has responded atleast once to the consumer in MessageRecords table from LivePerson Messaging API Source. Code logic: In MessageRecords, group by conversationId and participantId and calculate the MsgCount. Then join it with MessagingInteractions table based on conversationId and particpantId-assignedAgentId and set IsEngaged to 1 if MsgCount>0 else 0.

This attribute is calculated using columns conversationId,participantId,time columns coming from ConsumerParticipants section in LivePerson Messaging API source. Logic:Flag to determine whether same consumer participated in different conversation within 60 minutes from  LivePerson Messaging API Source. Code logic: In ConsumerParticipants, group by conversationId and participantId and calculate the min(time). Then using lag function,partition by participantId, order by min(time) and calculate the timedifference between subsequent conversations opened by same participantId. If timedifference<=60, then IsRepeatContact is hardcoded as 1 in last InteractiveSequence record of respective conversation.

Derived by applying decode logic on Reason column coming from Transfers section in LivePerson MessagingInteraction API source. Logic: Flag Set to 1 for agent transfer reason is agent. It means the conversation was transferred to a specific agent. Code Logic - Hardcoded as 1 if Reason='agent' otherwise hardcoded as 0.

Derived by applying decode logic on conversationId, interactivesequence,interactionTime columns from Interaction section , time column from MessageRecords section and endTime column from Info section in LivePerson MessagingInteraction API source. Logic: Count of messages exchanged during each assigned Agent Interaction segment of the conversation. codeLogic: In Interactions table, use lead function on interactionTime, partition By conversationId based on which interactiontimeLead column is generated which provides assignment time of next interaction of that conversation. If it is the last interactive sequence then interactiontimeLead will be endTime of the conversation. Join it with MessageRecords table and count the number of messages transferred where time falls between InteractionTime and interactiontimeLead.

derived by applying decode logic on conversationId,assignedAgentId,assignedAgentLoginName columns from Interaction section, time,sentBy,participantId columns from MessageRecords section in LivePerson Messaging Interaction API source. logic: Flag Set to true if first human agent responds within 3 minutes after Bot last interaction  from LivePerson Messaging API Source. codeLogic: Step1: Derive FirstHumanResponseTime: join Interactions and MessageRecords based on conversationId,participantId. filter where assignedAgentLoginName not like '%bot%'. Group by conversationId and calculate min(time) Step2: Derive BotMaxResponseTime - do the same join as mentioned, filter where assignedAgentLoginName like '%bot%'. Group by conversationId and calculate max(time).Step 3: Derive IsWithinSLA: hardcoded as 1 if ResponseFromAgentInSeconds(Time at which very first Human agent responded - Bot Agent's Last Message time) <= 180 seconds

Derived by applying decode logic on time,targetskillName column in Transfers,participantId,userTypeName columns in AgentParticipants,time, sentBy columns in MessageRecords,closeReason column Info sections coming from LivePerson MessagingInteraction API. This flag is populated only for last human skill Interactive Sequence.
Logic:
Step 1: Derive LastHumanSkillTransferTime: in Transfers, get record by last human skill transfer by partition by conversationId aggregated by max(time) where targetskillName not like %bot% or null.
Step2:remove bot agent messages -  join MessageRecords with AgentParticipants on conversationId,participantIdand where ~(sentBy=agent and userTypeName!='human')
Step 3: In MessageRecords, Calculate FirstResponseTime of Agent and Customer after LastHumanSkillTransferTime.
Step 4: Apply Casecondition for IsInteractive -
a) when Human Agent responds within 3 minutes from time it was transferred to human skill and there is No customer response, IsInteractive=0
b) Customer closes the conversation(closeReason='consumer') in less than 3 minutes from time it was transferred to human skill and there is No Human Agent response, IsInteractive is hardcoded as 0.
c)In all other scenarios, IsInteractive is hardcoded as 1.

Step 2 - If category is null and campaignEngagementName like '%button%' or when category like '%button%' then Hardcoded as 1 otherwise hardcoded as 0.
Direct mapping to SessionID column coming from Info section of LivePerson MessaginInteraction API source.

Derived by applying complex decode logic on time column coming from MessageRecords section from LivePersonMessaging API source to calculate Avg Wait Time for Consumer Response after Agent Message. Logic:  (sum(TimeGap)/count(TimeGap)) where TimeGap is wait time for consumer message after agent's message.In other words, TimeGap=time difference of (consumer message time - time of agent's message just prior to consumer message).  This value is Populated at Last Interactive Sequence of each ConversationId.

Indirect Mapping of ServiceActivityTopicKey column in the DimServiceActivityTopic entity, by grouping Topic section coming from LivePerson MessagingInteraction API source on conversationId, select topic with min(originalTimeStamp). Derived by applying complex decode logic on time column coming from Transfers section from LivePersonMessaging API source.Logic: This is duration in seconds from Agent's assignment time to the conversation till the next transfer/end time of the conversation. code Logic: Step 1: join Interactions and Transfers table based on conversationId,Interactions.assginedAgentId=Transfers.sourceAgentId,ChatBeginDateTime<Transfers.time. Step 2: use lead function on ChatBeginDateTime with partitioned by conversationId, interactiveSequence so that AgentSegmentEndTime=Transfers.time and info.conversationEndTime in case it is the last InteractiveSequence of the conversation. Step 3: Calculate Time difference in seconds between AgentSegmentEndTime and ChatBeginDateTime.

derived by applying decode logic on conversationId,assignedAgentId,assignedAgentLoginName columns from Interaction section, time,sentBy,participantId columns from MessageRecords section in LivePerson Messaging Interaction API source. Logic: Time taken(in seconds) for Human Agent to respond after Bot agent's last response.Populated only at First Human Agent Interaction grain of respective conversation. Derived from FirstHumanResponse and BotMaxHumanResponse column coming from LivePerson Messaging API source as ( Time at which very first Human agent responded - Bot Agent's Last Message time). codeLogic: Derive FirstHumanResponseTime: join Interactions and MessageRecords based on conversationId,participantId. filter where assignedAgentLoginName not like '%bot%'. Group by conversationId and calculate min(time) Step2: Derive BotMaxResponseTime - do the same join as mentioned, filter where assignedAgentLoginName like '%bot%'. Group by conversationId and calculate max(time).Step 3: Derive FirstHumanResponseInSeconds: time difference between FirstHumanResponseTime and BotMaxResponseTime in seconds.

Step 2:When Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon is 1,hardcoded Status attribute as Connected, and when Status is Connected hardcoded IsAccepted as 1
Step 3: Creating WaitSeconds column by applying logic like Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and Session.msdyn_sessioncreatedon and
Total time gap between Session.msdyn_agentacceptedon and OCLiveWorkitem.msdyn_createdon ,and unioning all the data,and renaming WaitSeconds *1000 to WaitTimeInMilliSeconds
Step 4: Case When IsAccepted is 1 and WaitTimeInMilliSeconds >0 then col WaitTimeInMilliSeconds will populate as MilliSecondsToAccept otherwise hardcoded as 0
Step 5: For Rave Source It is derived from time gap between RaveSupportRequestDetails.AcknowledgeDateTime and RaveSupportRequestDetails.CreateDateTime logic:
(AcknowledgeDateTime-CreateDateTime)
Step 6: For Directly source it is derived from time gap between CreatedDate and FirstResponseTime and converting it into milli seconds (CreatedDate-FirstResponseTime)*1000

column4:
Derived by applying decode logic on UnitsSold coming from FactRevenue present in UDPMLGCS DataMart and ServiceLineName,FullName,MasterSite,SolutionType,DataSourceName,BusinessSegment & ProductFamily columns from DimServiceLine, DimSupportQueue, DimVendorSite, DimSolutionType, DimDataSource, DimSupportQueue & DimSupportAreaPath tables coming from UDP Consumer within SA&DP.
Logic: If ~(lower('DimServiceLine.ServiceLineName').like('%smb%'))
       and ~(lower('DimSupportQueue.FullName').like('%smb%'))
       and ~(lower('DimVendorSite.MasterSite').isin('wcs', 'web sales support'))
       and (lower('DimSolutionType.SolutionType').isin('product'))
       and (col('m.UnitsSold')> -1)
       and ~(lower('DimDataSource.DataSourceName').isin('chinasmb'))
	   then HardCoded as "Store"
	   Else If lower('DimSupportQueue.BusinessSegment')=='mast'
	   then HardCoded as 'Advertiser'
	   Else If lower('DimSupportAreaPath.ProductFamily')=='microsoft 365 consumer retention'
       then HardCoded as 'SaveDesk' 
       Otherwise HardCoded as 'Unspecified' gives BusinessSegment
Logic 2: BusinessSegment joined with DimBusinessSegmentUnit by BusinessSegment from both tables and selected BusinessSegmentUnitKey

column4: Derived by applying decode logic on Vendor column in WLSC table coming from ACSR API Source. Logic: when Vendor='msa cnx - megamall' then 'Convergys', when Vendor='msa cnx - kuala lumpur' then 'Convergys', when Vendor='msa tck - seoul' then 'TCK', when Vendor='msa rck - okinawa' then 'Moshi Moshi Hotline', when Vendor='msa cnx - shaw' then 'Convergys' otherwise Vendor

column4: This is a reference key to DimTime table to get created time details of ACSRIssue in UTC. This key is populated by joining the CreatedDateFormatted from source with Time in the DimTime
column5: Abdul

column4: Derived by applying decode logic on RecoveryFailureReason,StatusCode,HasFailedThreeTimes,ValidationVerdict,IsDuplicateRequestEmail columns in WLSC table coming from ACSR API Source.  Logic: when RecoveryFailureReason in (164950000, 164950002, 164950003) then '[No Level 4 Issue Code]', when StatusCode ='164950000' then 'Failed 1st', when HasFailedThreeTimes='true' then 'Failed 3rd or More', when ValidationVerdict='164950001' then 'Pass - Reset Link Sent', when IsDuplicateRequestEmail='true' then 'Duplicate Submission' otherwise RecoveryFailureReason
column5: Abdul

column4: Derived by applying decode logic on Createddate,Closeddate columns in WLSC table coming from ACSR API Source. Logic: when time difference (in minutes ) of Createddate,Closeddate <=120 then 'Closed < 2 Hrs', when time difference is between 120 and 240 then 'Closed < 4 Hrs', when time difference is between 240 and 480 then 'Closed < 8 Hrs', when time difference <=1440 then 'Closed < 24 Hrs', when time difference >1440 then 'Closed > 24 Hrs' otherwise NULL
column5: Abdul

column4: Derived by applying decode logic on Advocate column in WLSC table coming from ACSR API Source. Logic: when Advocate has string '#' derive characters after string'#' otherwise populate data in Advocate

                        (col('ticketnumber').cast('long').isNotNull())
                      )

(CaseEventsIncremental_AddedColumns.join(

                          .select(CaseEventsIncremental_AddedColumns["*"], "DS.DataSourceKey")
                              .withColumn( "ServiceRequestKey",
                                            concat(
                                                col("ServiceRequestID").cast("string"),
                                                col("DS.DataSourceKey").cast("string"),
                                                  ).cast("long")
                              ).drop("DataSourceKey")
                    )
